    function's behaviour. The :data:`GLib.SpawnFlags.DO_NOT_REAP_CHILD` means that the
    child will not automatically be reaped; you must use a child watch
    (g_child_watch_add()) to be notified about the death of the child process,
    otherwise it will stay around as a zombie process until this process exits.
    Eventually you must call :func:`GLib.spawn_close_pid` on the ``child_pid``, in order to
    free resources which may be associated with the child process. (On Unix,
    using a child watch is equivalent to calling waitpid() or handling
    the ``SIGCHLD`` signal manually. On Windows, calling :func:`GLib.spawn_close_pid`
    is equivalent to calling ``CloseHandle()`` on the process handle returned
    in ``child_pid``). See g_child_watch_add().

